I think it looks good, but since I'm not really familiar with the scope, a few questions that may help me understand the change better:
1. Why were the two cases separated into an `if-else` in the first place? A comment from the pre-change era indicates it was a performance consideration, is this the case here?
2. This section is identically changed in both streaming and batch translators, right? (while it would be nice to remove the duplication here, I'm not hinting it should be done as part of this commit, just making sure I don't miss anything since they look very similar)
3. Did you have a chance to test this on an actual cluster?

> Why were the two cases separated into an if-else in the first place? A comment from the pre-change era indicates it was a performance consideration, is this the case here?

The SDK used to have two different `PTransform`s, `ParDo.Bound` and `ParDo.BoundMulti` and so the runner had two separate translations.
> This section is identically changed in both streaming and batch translators, right? (while it would be nice to remove the duplication here, I'm not hinting it should be done as part of this commit, just making sure I don't miss anything since they look very similar)

Yes, this is something we unfortunately can escape because Spark uses different APIs for batch and streaming - the `RDD` API and the `DStream` API.
> Did you have a chance to test this on an actual cluster?

No, there's nothing new here in terms of the Spark graph.. no new/different usage.
